{"summary":"I would accept all four amendments. The strongest issues are the duplicate terminal journal-entry bug and the paused-state clobber during reconciliation; the other two are worthwhile maintainability/test-robustness fixes.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-8-841107a4","decision":"accept","rationale":"`current_bead_runs` is already the result of `latest_task_runs_per_bead`, so passing it into `active_bead_ids` re-runs the same collapse for no semantic benefit. Filtering `current_bead_runs` directly is equivalent, removes redundant work, and makes the invariant clearer at the call site."},{"amendment_id":"fr-8-7e4d3238","decision":"accept","rationale":"The helper silently changes behavior after its first `with_milestone_write_lock` call because both channels are consumed with `take()`. That is a fragile hidden contract for a type that implements the full trait; making the single-use nature explicit, ideally with an assertion, reduces the risk of future concurrency tests passing for the wrong reason."},{"amendment_id":"fr-8-beaac5f9","decision":"accept","rationale":"This is a real idempotency bug. Terminal replay/backfill is intentionally supported for an already-finalized attempt, but journal deduplication keys on the full `details` string. If a replay only adds missing `plan_hash` or `outcome_detail`, it describes the same completion yet no longer matches the original event, so a duplicate `BeadCompleted`/`BeadFailed` entry is appended."},{"amendment_id":"fr-8-3e84cce1","decision":"accept","rationale":"`Paused` is a distinct lifecycle state and should not be treated as interchangeable with `Ready`. The current reconciliation logic rewrites a non-terminal paused milestone to `Ready` whenever there are prior task runs but no active bead, so completion repair/backfill can silently clear an operator-imposed pause."}]}